# Fluff Date: 2026-02-10 14:00:04
overview:<p>The Arion is a 35-ton light QuadVee developed by Clan Hell's Horses during the early 3130s at the Csesztreg Industriplex Alpha Annex on Csesztreg. Named for the divine horse of Greek mythology, the Arion was designed as a fast-moving harasser capable of using its limited weaponry to engage enemy units at range. As one of three production-model QuadVees first fielded in 3136 alongside the Cyllaros and Harpagos, the Arion represented an effort to refine the experimental QuadVee concept pioneered by the Boreas prototype into a viable light combat platform. Despite its speed and unique conversion capabilities, the Arion's constrained payload left many Hell's Horses warriors questioning both the design's individual merits and the viability of the entire QuadVee program.</p>

capabilities:<p>Powered by a 210-rated Light Force fusion engine, the Arion achieves a maximum speed of 97 kilometers per hour in either its quadrupedal 'Mech or tracked vehicle form, making it the fastest QuadVee in the Hell's Horses touman. The dual-pilot cockpit arrangement allows the dedicated gunner to engage targets independently while the driver manages terrain and mode transitions. Like all QuadVees, the Arion's turret-like torso provides a full 360-degree firing arc, a significant tactical advantage over conventional bipedal designs.</p><p>The primary armament consists of a Series 7K extended-range large laser supplemented by a pair of Type 1 Cross-Pattern SRM-4 launchers, giving the design a mix of long-range precision and close-range punch. However, the conversion equipment, dual cockpit, and tracks consume significant tonnage, leaving the Arion with precious little room for weapons and engine power. The result is a light 'Mech that can be outpaced by modern mediums and outgunned by vehicles lighter than itself. Compound H17 ferro-fibrous armor provides reasonable protection for its weight class, though concentrated fire remains a serious threat.</p>

deployment:<p>No factory variants of the Arion are currently produced. The sole production model mounts a fixed weapons configuration centered on its Series 7K extended-range large laser and paired short-range missile launchers. While the design's limited payload has prevented significant diversification, the Arion's unified cockpit arrangement serves as a maturation of the QuadVee dual-pilot concept over the Cyllaros's problematic divided crew stations. The Hell's Horses have deployed the Arion exclusively within their own touman, with no other Clan expressing interest in acquiring the design.</p>

history:<p>The Arion first saw combat as part of an all-QuadVee Binary during a Trial of Possession against Clan Jade Falcon on Derf in 3136. This engagement, which pitted the untested QuadVee concept against a conventional Jade Falcon force, ended poorly for the Horses as four of five QuadVees were destroyed. The Binary's failure owed less to any individual design's shortcomings than to the warriors' inexperience with the unique tactical demands of hybrid 'Mech-vehicle combat.</p><p>The design found better results during the defense of Weingarten in 3139, when elements of the Rasalhague Dominion's Second Tyr Assault Cluster raided the planet. A mixed Star of Arions and Harpagoses played an effective support role, with the QuadVees' broad firing fields and rapid mode transitions helping convince the attackers they faced a larger force than was actually present. The Second Tyr briefly believed they were engaging two Stars rather than one.</p><p>A less successful deployment came during the 91st Mechanized Assault Cluster's raid on the Dominion world of Gunzburg in 3143, where a vehicle Star including a pair of Arions was hammered by the Second Freemen Cluster's artillery. The QuadVees were forced to break ranks and abandon their disabled brethren, though their ability to convert to 'Mech mode and withdraw under their own power demonstrated the very survival advantages the concept was designed to provide.</p><p>The Arion has seen continued service in Hell's Horses second-line Galaxies, typically deployed alongside other QuadVee designs in mixed formations that exploit the Horses' long tradition of blurring the lines between 'Mech and vehicle units.</p>

